<p><a href="http://www.philipebert.info/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Philip A. Ebert</a>, currently professor of philosophy at the <a href="https://www.stir.ac.uk/about/faculties/arts-humanities/law-and-philosophy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">University of Stirling</a>, has accepted an offer from the <a href="https://www.plus.ac.at/philosophy-gw/?lang=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">University of Salzburg</a>, where he will be professor of theoretical philosophy.<span id="more-55525"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-55526 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ebert-philip.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="400" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ebert-philip.jpg 400w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ebert-philip-300x300.jpg 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ebert-philip-150x150.jpg 150w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ebert-philip-177x177.jpg 177w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ebert-philip-380x380.jpg 380w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></p>
<p>Professor Ebert works on various topics in epistemology (especially risk and rationality), early analytic philosophy (especially Frege), philosophy of mathematics (especially abstractionism), and philosophical issues in behavioral science. In recent years he was one of the leaders of the &#8220;<a href="http://www.varietiesofrisk.info/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Varieties of Risk</a>&#8221; project and produced a film that brought together <a href="https://dailynous.com/2019/10/28/philosophy-and-skiing/">philosophy and extreme skiing</a>. You can learn more about his writings <a href="https://philpeople.org/profiles/philip-a-ebert" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> and <a href="https://philpeople.org/profiles/philip-a-ebert" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p>He takes up his new position at Salzburg in February, 2026.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/11/06/ebert-from-stirling-to-salzburg/">Ebert from Stirling to Salzburg</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>